Obtained the data in shp format from the following: 
http://thematicmapping.org/downloads/world_borders.php

Coverted the data from shp format into geojson using qjis 
instructions here: 
http://gis.stackexchange.com/questions/91812/convert-shapefiles-to-geojson

To test your geojson, use this drag and drop service by google maps:
https://developers.google.com/maps/documentation/javascript/examples/layer-data-dragndrop

For checking if a point is inside a geojson polygon or multipolygon:
http://turfjs.org/static/docs/module-turf_inside.html

For generating a polygon of desired dimensions:
http://turfjs.org/static/docs/module-turf_polygon.html
or more conveniently:
http://turfjs.org/static/docs/module-turf_envelope.html



